en_420631_0	Concerned about the hardships due to scarcity of water, 7 Sri Lanka National Guard troops of the 652 Brigade of the 65 Division under the Security Force Headquarters - Kilinochchi extending their hands of friendship to civilians began a mobile project to provide them with drinking water using Army bowsers.
en_420631_1	More than 55 affected families in Arogyapuram area received drinking water thanks to the Army mobile service The community project which began on Thursday (27) is still continuing once a day with the blessings of Major General G V Ravipriya, Commander Security Forces Kilinochchi and under the close supervision of Major General Wasantha Kumarapperuma, General Officer Commanding of 65 Division.
